# WhatsApp Integration Rules

When working with the Meta WhatsApp Cloud API in this project, adhere strictly to the following rules based on our established skill and architecture:

## 1. Webhook Payload Processing
- **No Manual JSON Parsing in Handlers**: All raw payload parsing MUST be strictly encapsulated within `IWhatsAppPayloadProcessor`. Wolverine Handlers should only rely on the strongly-typed `ProcessWhatsAppMessage` record.
- **Safe JSON Extraction**: Always use safe navigation and catch specific exceptions (e.g., `KeyNotFoundException`, `IndexOutOfRangeException`, `InvalidOperationException`) when reading the deeply nested `entry[0].changes[0].value.messages[0]` array, as some webhooks (like message delivery statuses) will not contain text data.
- **Stream Buffering**: Any endpoint computing the HMAC-SHA256 signature must call `request.EnableBuffering()` so the request body stream can be read a second time for JSON deserialization.

## 2. API Security
- **HMAC-SHA256 Validation**: Every incoming WhatsApp webhook `POST` request MUST be verified using the `X-Hub-Signature-256` header against the raw request body using the `WhatsApp_App_Secret`. No exceptions.
- **Challenge Verification**: The `GET` webhook endpoint must independently verify `hub.verify_token` against our server's `WhatsApp_Verify_Token` and return the raw `hub.challenge` string.

## 3. Outbound Message Dispatch
- **Authentication**: All `POST` requests to `https://graph.facebook.com/v19.0/{phone_number_id}/messages` must include the `Authorization: Bearer <WhatsApp_Access_Token>` header.
- **Payload Format**: Outbound Text messages must strictly follow this structure:
  ```json
  {
    "messaging_product": "whatsapp",
    "recipient_type": "individual",
    "to": "<phone_number>",
    "type": "text",
    "text": { "body": "Your message here" }
  }
  ```
- **Wolverine Dispatching**: Outbound messages should only be triggered by consuming a `ResponseGenerated` event via a Wolverine handler, decoupling the LLM generation phase from the actual HTTP dispatch phase.
